  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "body": "**What happened**:\r\n\r\nPod `foo` failed. I want to inspect the status of the pod, but getting the pod directly returns nothing.\r\n```console\r\n$ kubectl get pod foo\r\n$\r\n```\r\nAdding the `--show-all` (`-a`) option shows the pod.\r\n```console\r\n$ kubectl get pod foo -a\r\nNAME      READY     STATUS    RESTARTS   AGE\r\nfoo       0/1       Error     0          12m\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\n**What you expected to happen**:\r\n\r\nI understand by default `get pod` only shows non-terminated resources, but since I specified the pod name explicitly, I'd expect to get the pod regardless of its state.\r\n",
